HEADWORD: Exenterate
<hw>Ex*en"ter*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exenteratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exenterare</ets>; cf. Gr. <?/; <?/
out + <?/ intestine.]</ety> <def>To take out the bowels or entrails of;
to disembowel; to eviscerate; <as>as, <ex>exenterated</ex>
fishes</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Exenterated</qex> rule-mongers and eviscerated logicians.</q>
<rj><qau>Hare.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exenteration</ent>⟦br⟧
